org.perfcake.reporting.destination

Class ElasticsearchDestination

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.perfcake.reporting.destination.AbstractDestination
      • org.perfcake.reporting.destination.ElasticsearchDestination
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable, Destination

    public class ElasticsearchDestination
extends AbstractDestination
    Writes the resulting data to Elasticsearch using a simple HTTP REST client. The reported data have information about the test progress (time in milliseconds since start, percentage and iteration), real time of each result, and the complete results map. Quantities are stored without their unit. To properly search through the data, we need to set the mapping (to be able to interpret time as time). However, this needs to be done just once for each index and type.
    Author:
    Martin Večeřa
